The European Union changes the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the Visa Applicants Service centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost of waiting will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing visas at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit themselves to the Visa Applicants Service Centres (ASC) prior to their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will receive biometric information from the applicant, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have some benefits for aspirants, including the following:
The total cost of treating the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment to obtain a meeting, another payment for the processing of the visa and another for the mail service to deliver the document.
The aspirant will make a unique payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas on request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visas.
Persons wishing to renew their visas will not be required to submit to an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only submit to the closer ASC where they will submit the documents and their fingerprints will be taken.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be included in the ASC, applicants wishing to meet for a second meeting to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain there less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants at the Consulates of Ciudad Ju√°rez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra 26-dollar service fee.
For further information on the new procedure for requesting visa, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/balletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
